stylometry: Safety stock is the amount of inventory you should keep on hand for the time between ordering and delivery of your next shipment. That way you can have a cushion to keep you from having a stock-out and not being able to meet demand while waiting for your next shipment to come in. To find the best amount of safety stock, it is important to know the EDDLT (estimated demand during lead time) so you can best estimate how large your demand will be while waiting for the next shipment to come in. If you were to not keep safety stock on hand, you may find yourself stocking-out more often, and potentially loosing customer's loalty since you can't be trusted to keep inventory on hand.
